cs.IT, cs.GT, cs.LG, cs.CR, cs.SY

The paper deals with a game-theoretic framework for hypothesis testing, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and game theory (cs.GT). The concept of indistinguishability region is related to statistical learning theory (cs.LG), while the use of training sequences and the presence of an adversary suggest a focus on security and cryptography (cs.CR) and control systems (cs.SY).
